Shoe Bend on Sir Lowry's Pass on the N2 in the Helderberg area on Thursday. - Are you there?  Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos. The City of Cape Town's fire and rescue services asked for
aerial support after the extensive vegetation fire was reported in the early
hours of the morning, spokesperson Liezl Moodie said. One lane of the N2 towards Grabouw was closed.  Nine firefighting vehicles were on the scene and no property
was currently in danger. The cause of the blaze had not yet been determined.      24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  